                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1949v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1211</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1211</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1949-09-16T19:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1949-09-16T19:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="1211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1211">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.633/9–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-16T20:00:00-04:00">September 16, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>641. Reurtels 1542 and 1549 Sept 14 and 15.<note n="89" xml:id="d1211fn89">Neither printed.</note> Press release issued<note n="90" xml:id="d1211fn90">Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, September 26, 1949, p.
                        482.</note> Deptel 634 rptd Nanking 1100 Sept 15.</p>
                <pb facs="0989" n="979" xml:id="pg_979"/>
                <p>You are authorized send letter to Chu in ur discretion. Send Dept complete text
                    such letter if and when sent for Dept’s use in press release if deemed desirable
                    at time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
